Furniture For You

Modern furniture refers to furniture produced from the late 19th century through the present that is influenced by modernism. Post-World War II ideals of cutting excess, commodification, and practicality of materials in design heavily influenced the aesthetic of the furniture.It was a tremendous departure from all furniture design that had gone before it.
There was an opposition to the decorative arts, which included Art Nouveau, Neoclassical, and Victorian styles.
